<bioghist encodinganalog="545"><p>Einar Kvaran worked in the warehouse at the People's Wherehouse Food Co-Op.  Following the unionization of its work force, Mr. Kvaran became a steward in the Industrial Workers of the World, Local 660.</p></bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520"><p>The Kvaran papers are a rich source for information about the operation and unionization of the food co-op.  The collection has been subdivided into two series: Michigan Federation of Food Co-op's The People's Wherehouse and The People's Wherehouse IWW Local 660.  The first series contains information about the day-to-day operations of the warehouse and the eventual demise of the co-op.  The latter series contains information about the union formed by the workers of the PWC.  Included are the contract negotiations of the union, the by-laws and information about the legal battle between the Local 660 and the PWC management over unfair labor negotiations.</p></scopecontent>

